# Phase 10: Logistics & Hardware Interfacing Simulation

Transform the Processing Center from a standard web form into a high-fidelity **Command Console** that simulates real-time interfacing with physical border hardware (Document Readers, Biometric Scanners, and System Telemetry).

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> This phase introduces "Hardware Dependency". If the simulated hardware status reports a failure, the officer will be unable to process travelers until a "Calibration" action is performed.

## Proposed Changes

### [Backend] Hardware Telemetry Simulation

#### [MODIFY] [server.js](file:///c:/Users/Mohammed/.gemini/antigravity/ics-backend/server.js)
- Add `GET /api/hardware/status`: Returns simulated health for `doc_reader`, `bio_camera`, and `sys_link`.
- Add `GET /api/hardware/mrz-scan`: Returns a random high-fidelity traveler profile (name, passport, dob) to simulate a physical passport scan.
- Add `POST /api/hardware/calibrate`: Logs a technician event and "repairs" the simulated hardware.

---

### [Frontend] Augmented Command Interface

#### [MODIFY] [Processing.jsx](file:///c:/Users/Mohammed/.gemini/antigravity/ics-frontend/src/pages/Processing.jsx)
- **Status Dashboard**: Add a header row showing real-time hardware heartbeat icons.
- **MRZ Ingestion**: Add a "Quick Scan Passport" button that triggers the `/api/hardware/mrz-scan` endpoint and auto-populates the form with a simulated typing effect.
- **Logistics Feed**: Add a vertical scrolling "System Log" in the sidebar showing background technical events.
- **Operational Lock**: Disable the "Process Traveler" button if the `doc_reader` status is `Offline`.

#### [MODIFY] [Processing.css](file:///c:/Users/Mohammed/.gemini/antigravity/ics-frontend/src/pages/Processing.css) (or add inline)
- Add "Matrix-style" scrolling animation for the logistics feed.
- Add glow effects for "Online" hardware indicators.

## Open Questions

- Should the "Hardware Failure" be random (e.g., 5% chance on page load) or purely triggered via the UI for demonstration?
- Do we want to simulate "Thermal Printing" of the visa receipt after a successful clearance?

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- Verify `/api/hardware/status` returns valid JSON.
- Verify `/api/hardware/mrz-scan` returns one of the 5 mock test profiles.

### Manual Verification
- Navigate to Processing.
- Click "Quick Scan Passport" and verify the form fills automatically.
- Check the "Logistics Feed" for simulated heartbeat messages.
- Simulate a hardware failure and verify the "Process" button locks correctly.
